article.headline: Cornell 79, Army 66
article.story: ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) -- Ka'Ron Barnes scored 24 points and Lenny Collins added 18 to lead Cornell to a 79-66 over Army Saturday night. Eric Taylor had 15 points as the Big Red (1-2) won its first game at the neutral-site at Blue Cross Arena, after opening the season with losses to Georgia Tech and Colgate. Josh Wilson led the Black Knights (2-2) with 21 points. Cornell scored the game's first five points and never trailed, although Army tied the game twice. It was 36-33 at halftime, and that's as close as Army got the rest of the way. Barnes scored 15 points in the first half alone on 4-of-7 shooting. He has scored in double figures in 14 consecutive games dating back to last season. Barnes never committed a turnover in 39 minutes of action while recording three steals and three assists. Army stayed close in the second half but never took a lead. Cornell's lead was down to 54-48 at the 10:00 mark when the Big Red reeled off seven unanswered points to take control. Collins scored on a layup with 3:16 remaining to give Cornell its biggest lead at 69-53.
